text: Jorge Mariné (24 September 1941 – 22 February 2025) was a Spanish cyclist. He competed in the individual road race at the 1964 Summer Olympics. He was born in Vinyols i els Arcs, Spain. Mariné died on 22 February 2025, at the age of 83.Mor Jordi Mariné Tarés, exciclista professional i persona molt vinculada a la vida associativa i política cambrilenca ==References== Category:1941 births Category:2025 deaths Category:Spanish cyclists Category:Olympians for Spain
